Bike for Bovines
description: Mountain Bike Race to benefit the Stonewall Farm Learning Center and World Bicycle Relief
course: Approx. 13 miels of rough logging roads, some wet bogs, sweet single track, dirt road and downhill ending with a half mile of railroad bed.  Slightly over 2000 feet of total climbing.  http://connect.garmin.com/activity/585117  Beginner course will be slightly modified
registration: Pre register and save $7 at www.bikereg.com by 7/29/2011 or register day of.  All non USA Cycling licensed racers will be charged $5 for a one day membership
directions:
From the North, South or East of Keene  Take insections wheter Rte 101 ends and Rte 9/10/12 combine to bypass Keene, take Rte 9 West for approx 3 miles.  A blue state sign bearing Stonewall Farm\'s name will alert you to right turn onto Chesterfield Rd.  Approx. 1 mile on chesterfield Rd. turn right into driveway at the bend in the road.  The Sugarhouse and Learning Center will be in front of you.
From Vermont Exit 3 off intersstate 91.  Follow Rte 9 for approx. 11 miles, looking for a blue state sign bearing Stonewall Farm\'s name which will direct you to turn left onto Chesterfield Road.  Follow Chesterfield Road for approx. 1 mile and turn right onto driveway Sugarhouse and Learning Center will be right in front of you.

title: Hopkinton (N.H.) Rotary Club Time Trial
description: A rolling 19.5 mile time trial in rural NH countryside for solo riders, tandems, and 2-person teams of various ages and mixed genders,
course: Course begins at intersection of US I-89 and NH Route 103; proceeds approximately 10 miles past Lake Winnepocket to Blackwater Dam turnaround; and returns.
registration: On-line registration thru BikeReg closes May 14; on-site day of event registration includes $10 surcharge. One-day USA cycling license required for non-licensed riders.
notes: This event is designed to appeal to licensed and non-licensed riders, with merchandise prizes for various age categories, including solo riders, tandems, and 2-person teams.
directions: From south of Concord NH, take I-93 north to I-89; west on I-89 to Exit 7; follow signs for \"Time Trial.\" From north of Concord NH, take I-93 south to I-89; west on I-89 and proceed as above.

title: Cyclocross at White Park
description: Cycloross race at White Park in Concord NH. This is the park that the Concord Crit circles every. It is going to be a great venue with many challenges.
course: 2.5k course around the interior of White Park. A fast grassy course, one short pavement section with a \"memorable\" run up all within the confines of Whites Park.  Our first year please come support a NH race and look forward to many years to come.

title: Shoot the Loop Time Trial
description: a rolling 15mi Time Trial in Peterborough NH
course: The start is located at the Eastern Mountain Sports location at 1 Vose farm Rd. in Peterborough NH and heads East on Rt 202. Turn right on Forrest Rd. and follow 5 mi to the inter sefction of Rt 136. Take a Right turn on Rt 136 and follow back to Rt 202. Take a Right on 202 and back to the Start Finish area
registration:
Register on line at Bikereg.com or mail entries to Eastern Mountain Sports, Store 21 Attn: Shoot The Loop, 1 Vose Farfm Rd. Peterborough, NH 03458 
All checks Payable to: Eastern Mountain Sports
notes: This is a fast rolling course with three right hand turns.
directions:
Directions: 
From the East 101W to 202N (2.7 Mi. on right)
From the West 101E to 202N (2.7 Mi. on right)
From the North Rt 9/202S to Peterborough NH 2 Mi after town line on Left

title: Attitash & Cranmore Mountain Cross Country and Dow
Krempels King of the Road Challenge
description: The Krempels King of the Road Challenge is a fund-raising bicycle ride to benefit the Krempels Center. The ride features the support and involvement of the renowned bike-racing brothers Teddy and Robbie King.
course: The event will feature loops for varying abilities, with approximate distances of 55, 30 and 15 miles. Course maps will be posted on the event web site.
registration: Registration for the event and fund-raising will be available on the event web site.
directions: The event will start & finish at the Timberland facility located at 200 Domain Drive in Stratham NH. Directions will be provided on the event web site.
